description: From Middle English inmateriall, from Medieval Latin immāteriālis.

adjectives.description: immaterial (comparative more immaterial, superlative most immaterial)

examples: Because ghosts are immaterial, they can pass through walls.

entries.meaning: (figurative) So insubstantial as to be irrelevant.
examples: Objection, Your Honour! The defendant's criminal record is immaterial to this case.
